  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the most family-friendly workplaces in Oakland?",
  "response": "Oakland, California, is home to several family-friendly workplaces that prioritize work-life balance, parental support, and inclusive benefits. Here are some notable examples:\n\n### 1. **Kaiser Permanente**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** Kaiser offers generous parental leave, flexible work schedules, on-site child care, and wellness programs. They also provide resources for parents, including lactation rooms and parenting workshops.\n   - **Industry:** Healthcare.\n\n### 2. **Clorox Company**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** Clorox offers paid parental leave, flexible work arrangements, and adoption assistance. They also have a strong emphasis on diversity, equity, and inclusion, making it a supportive environment for families.\n   - **Industry:** Consumer Goods.\n\n### 3. **Pandora (SiriusXM)**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** Pandora provides paid parental leave, flexible work hours, and a family-oriented culture. They also host events for employees and their families, fostering a sense of community.\n   - **Industry:** Media and Technology.\n\n### 4. **Blue Shield of California**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** Blue Shield offers comprehensive parental leave, adoption assistance, and flexible work options. They also provide mental health resources and family wellness programs.\n   - **Industry:** Healthcare and Insurance.\n\n### 5. **Mills College (now part of Northeastern University)**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** As an educational institution, Mills offers flexible schedules, family events, and access to campus resources like child care and educational programs.\n   - **Industry:** Education.\n\n### 6. **Oakland Unified School District (OUSD)**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** OUSD provides family-friendly schedules, paid time off, and access to educational resources for employees' children. They also prioritize community and family engagement.\n   - **Industry:** Education.\n\n### 7. **Patagonia (Oakland Store and HQ proximity)**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** Patagonia is known for its family-friendly policies, including paid parental leave, on-site child care, and flexible schedules. Their commitment to work-life balance is exceptional.\n   - **Industry:** Retail and Outdoor Gear.\n\n### 8. **Energy Solutions**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** This company offers flexible work arrangements, paid parental leave, and a supportive culture that values family time. They also prioritize sustainability, which can resonate with families.\n   - **Industry:** Environmental Services.\n\n### 9. **Oakland Athletics (A\u2019s)**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** The A\u2019s offer flexible schedules, family-friendly events, and a community-oriented workplace culture. They also provide opportunities for employees to bring their families to games.\n   - **Industry:** Sports and Entertainment.\n\n### 10. **Downtown Oakland YMCA**\n   - **Why it\u2019s family-friendly:** The YMCA offers flexible schedules, access to fitness facilities, and family-oriented programs. It\u2019s a great workplace for those who value community and wellness.\n   - **Industry:** Nonprofit and Community Services.\n\nThese workplaces stand out for their commitment to supporting families through policies and practices that make it easier for employees to balance their professional and personal lives. When considering family-friendly workplaces, it\u2019s always a good idea to research specific benefits and company culture to find the best fit for your needs.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
